DATA CLOUD
Web and Mobile Application Connector

Create data streams from your mobile apps and websites. You can query the data and activate it across mobile and email. Data Cloud ingests data from the website and mobile apps depending on the data type. Engagement data is collected every 15 minutes while profile data is collected every hour.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Connector Status for the Mobile App and Website
If you’re an admin for Data Cloud, you can see the status of your connector app on the app details page. The status indicates the current state of the connector app.
Connect Your Websites and Mobile Apps to Data Cloud
After you create your Data Cloud instance, connect your mobile applications and website source. By connecting your mobile applications and website sources, you can capture online data and control the scope of data ingestion and activation. After you set up the connector, create data streams before streaming events to your app.
Create a Web or Mobile App Data Stream
Create a data stream to begin the flow of data from a website or mobile app. Data Cloud ingests engagement data every 15 minutes and profile data every hour from the website and mobile apps.
Delete a Connector App
As an admin in Data Cloud, you can delete a mobile or a website connector app.
Mobile and Web SDK Schema Quick Guide for Data Cloud
A Mobile and Web SDK schema is a collection of event definitions used in Data Cloud. You can find more examples of the schema in Data Cloud API Developer Guide.
Starter Web and Mobile Connector Data Mappings
Before you can start using your data for segmentation and activation, the ingested data must be mapped to a canonical model. This mapping is done on the Data Mapping Canvas. Use these tables for recommendations on how to map the ingested data to the data model.
